# Test prompts for <skill-name>

Fixture for the improving-skills loop. Each row: a prompt and whether the
skill should fire.

Aim for ~10 positives and ~10 negatives. The negatives should be similar
enough to the positives that a vague description would fire on both — they
exist to penalize over-broad descriptions.

Format: `should-fire | prompt`

## Positive (should fire)

```
y | <prompt the skill should clearly handle>
y | <variant phrasing>
y | <edge case the skill should still catch>
```

## Negative (should NOT fire)

```
n | <prompt about an adjacent task that's NOT this skill's job>
n | <a vague request that could be misread as in-scope>
n | <a prompt this skill must decline so others can run>
```
